==English==

===Etymology===
From {{OF.}} ''[[mortier]]'', from {{L.}} ''[[mortarium]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈmɔːtɘ(ɹ)/}} {{SAMPA|/"mO:t@(r)/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{uncountable}} A mixture of [[lime]] or [[cement]], [[sand]] and [[water]] used for [[bonding]] [[brick]]s and [[stone]]s.
# {{countable}} [[Military]] A muzzle-loading, [[indirect]] fire weapon with either a [[rifle]]d or [[smooth]] [[bore]]. It usually has a shorter range than a howitzer, employs a higher angle of fire, and has a tube with a length of 10 to 20 calibers. See also [[gun]]; [[howitzer]]. JP-1-02.
# {{countable}} A hollow [[vessel]] used to [[pound]], [[crush]], [[rub]], [[grind]] or [[mix]] [[ingredient]]s with a [[pestle]].

